                  </persName>
             of it; he came and claimed the harness. We took the prisoner at the vinegar yard in St. John-street.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18070916-99-person890">
                  WILLIAM 
                  PERRY
               <interp inst="t18070916-99-person890" type="surname" value="PERRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18070916-99-person890" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18070916-99-person890" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a collar and harness maker, Islington Road. On Wednesday the latter end of August I had the harness to sell for the prisoner, he asked two pounds for it; on the Thursday the prosecutor claimed it. The harness is worth about thirty-six shillings.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18070916-99-person891">
                  CHARLES 
                  BROWN
               <interp inst="t18070916-99-person891" type="surname" value="BROWN"></interp>
